								<p align=LEFT style="margin-left: 0.7cm; margin-right: 0.7cm; font-weight: medium"><font color="#000000"><font size=3>Epicurus (c. 342-271 BC) founded <i>the</i> <i>Garden</i>, a combination of philosophical community and school. The residents of the <i>Garden</i> put Epicurus' teachings into practice. &quot;this man wears a wreath of oak leaves, the emblem of Pope Julius, to whose name Raphael dedicated the work signifying the golden age of this pontiff, his benefactor .(Some say that he is surrounded by a young and old man representing those who seriously followed his teachings.</font></font></p>
